Louisiana Purchase in 1803.

00:21:41.060 --> 00:21:44.050
Previous to that, it
was French-speaking.

00:21:44.050 --> 00:21:45.770
The name of it was La Charrette.

00:21:45.770 --> 00:21:49.110
By the time Lewis and Clark got
there it was Charrette Village,

00:21:49.110 --> 00:21:52.280
and the sign gives
the early history.

00:21:52.280 --> 00:21:56.490
So light bulb number
one went off in my head.

00:21:56.490 --> 00:21:58.620
This is Lewis and Clark territory.

00:21:58.620 --> 00:22:03.180
This is a story about
the westward frontier,

00:22:03.180 --> 00:22:08.330
about manifest destiny
in the next generation.

00:22:08.330 --> 00:22:13.590 position:56%
But another interesting piece on the
