to say to the kids is, you know,

00:43:56.950 --> 00:43:59.270
everybody here reads and writes.

00:43:59.270 --> 00:44:04.760
You have prospects, but Brown, by
contrast, like the vast majority

00:44:04.760 --> 00:44:07.370
of American slaves was illiterate,

00:44:07.370 --> 00:44:11.420
and in spite of a prodigious
intelligence,

00:44:11.420 --> 00:44:17.950
just extraordinary capacities,
he was a victim of slavery.

00:44:17.950 --> 00:44:21.460
And in many regards
a typical victim.

00:44:21.460 --> 00:44:26.230
And so part of the question
for me as a biographer,

00:44:26.230 --> 00:44:30.550
once he escaped was how
did he educate himself?

00:44:30.550 --> 00:44:32.580
How did he get educated?

00:44:32.580 --> 00:44:34.780
And there's no real evidence.

00:44:34.780 --> 00:44:40.580
I mean you have to make a lot of
guesses, and the answer that I came

00:44:40.580 --> 00:44:42.270
up with, which I'm pretty happy

00:44:42.270 --> 00:44:46.210
about until the negative
criticism starts coming in.

00:44:46.210 --> 00:44:50.380
I may have to rethink this, but
I think two things happened.

00:44:50.380 --> 00:44:52.730
Part of it was self-education.

00:44:52.730 --> 00:44:57.380
And this was a young man just
bursting with creative energies,

00:44:57.380 --> 00:45:01.850
and he wanted to learn, and
he had that inner spirit.

00:45:01.850 --> 00:45:06.080
But the other part, which I think
was actually also typical among

00:45:06.080 --> 00:45:09.490
African-Americans freed
or self freed

00:45:09.490 --> 00:45:13.740
from slavery was he was
educated by the community.

00:45:13.740 --> 00:45:17.200
The people around him, and
there actually is one tiny piece

00:45:17.200 --> 00:45:22.260
of evidence that Brown was
taught in part by his wife.

00:45:22.260 --> 00:45:27.400
He married a young woman in
Cleveland within six months

00:45:27.400 --> 00:45:30.100
or eight months of his escape.

00:45:30.100 --> 00:45:37.910
And I think it was a
communal enterprise,

00:45:37.910 --> 00:45:43.330
common that African-Americans
helped one another in many ways,

00:45:43.330 --> 00:45:46.500
but once chief way was
to become educated.

00:45:46.500 --> 00:45:48.670
And so I did look for
things like, you know,

00:45:48.670 --> 00:45:51.880
I looked up every African-American
in the city of Cleveland.

00:45:51.880 --> 00:45:58.580
There were only 50 or 60
when Brown got there in 1834,

00:45:58.580 --> 00:46:02.590
and looked for philanthropic
self-help organizations

00:46:02.590 --> 00:46:03.890
in Cleveland.

00:46:03.890 --> 00:46:07.860
In fact, African-Americans
were trying to start a school,

00:46:07.860 --> 00:46:12.500
so I think the story is
partially one of, you know,

00:46:12.500 --> 00:46:18.860
of individual initiative and the
other is communal responsibility.

