00:47:12.670 --> 00:47:15.680
because there were
no central archives,

00:47:15.680 --> 00:47:21.760 position:56%
and because Brown presumably -- this
was an important research question.

00:47:21.760 --> 00:47:24.680
What happened to Brown's archives?

00:47:24.680 --> 00:47:26.620
Brown was one of the best
read African-Americans

00:47:26.620 --> 00:47:28.180
in the United States.

00:47:28.180 --> 00:47:29.480
He read prodigiously.

00:47:29.480 --> 00:47:31.460
He must've had a large
library at home.

00:47:31.460 --> 00:47:36.540
He was a professional
writer for 40 years.

00:47:36.540 --> 00:47:40.780
He went from book to
book, and he updated them,

00:47:40.780 --> 00:47:49.470
which meant that he was
probably using earlier editions

00:47:49.470 --> 00:47:51.390
as manuscript copies.

00:47:51.390 --> 00:47:56.920
He had a prodigious correspondence.

00:47:56.920 --> 00:48:03.040
He was well known, lots of
friends, interesting friends.

00:48:03.040 --> 00:48:05.280
What happened to it all?

00:48:05.280 --> 00:48:08.120
And the answer is, we don't know.

00:48:08.120 --> 00:48:13.250
But the necessity therefore
