00:53:00.480 --> 00:53:09.480
Murray was a way of finding a
central figure in the history

00:53:09.480 --> 00:53:11.570
of the reputation

00:53:11.570 --> 00:53:14.710
of African-American
literature and culture.

00:53:14.710 --> 00:53:19.800
And of course the date of the Paris
exposition, 1900 was very nice.

00:53:19.800 --> 00:53:24.670
I said in my introduction that
Brown's reputation faded virtually

00:53:24.670 --> 00:53:28.190
into obscurity after
his death in the 1880's,

00:53:28.190 --> 00:53:32.080
and the reason was Jim Crow.

00:53:32.080 --> 00:53:33.710
That's an overstatement.

00:53:33.710 --> 00:53:37.300
Brown's reputation remained
alive in the black community,

00:53:37.300 --> 00:53:43.130
and Daniel Murray was very much
aware of Brown and Brown's peers.

00:53:43.130 --> 00:53:47.940
This was an amazing
generation, Brown, Jacobs,

00:53:47.940 --> 00:53:50.740
Taubman, Garnet, Delaney.

00:53:50.740 --> 00:53:53.470
